abstract.p:
The invention is directed to a pneumatic tire having a component comprising a vulcanizable rubber composition comprising, based on 100 parts by weight of elastomer (phr),
(A) from 35 to 65 phr of a solution polymerized styrene-butadiene rubber with a styrene content of from 38 to 50 percent by weight and a Tg of from -22°C to -10°C;
(B) from 10 to 35 phr of an emulsion or solution polymerized styrene-butadiene rubber with a styrene content of from 20 to 40 percent by weight and a Tg of from -55°C to -28°C;
(C) from 10 to 35 phr of polybutadiene; and
(D) from 10 to 100 phr of silica.

claim.claim-text:
The pneumatic tire of claim 1 or 2, wherein said component is selected
from the group consisting of tread cap, tread base, sidewall, apex, chafer,
sidewall insert, wirecoat and innerliner.
